<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Noto/Rep system.
There's bound to be a way to put those 2 together in a nice way with 1 color for the nice guys(red), the bad buys(blue), the thieves(grey) and the ones that just performed a criminal act.

Thieving.
Not to nerf it, but to actually make it an enojoyable experience. PvP thieves should be allowed.

Dungeon Themes.
They really need better ones.

Monster AI.
Do we not all agree? I kinda like being able to trap a monster to go to the loo for a while, but if it were smarter right from the beginning, I might like it otherwise.

Skills.
Add skills, combine skills, set skill relations, dump the stupid skill curve thing. Make skill gain 1000 times tougher than it is now (minus the enormous skill curve).
NOT implement RoT.

Macroing.
Never make it illegal, or just prevent it right from the beginnig.

Zero tolerance policy is a good idea.

Make T2A a patched expansion rather than an extra CD set.

Improve upon housing, rather than the current system. Have land up for sale instead. Allow houses to go vertical (and create a system to compensate for vertical expansion.) 1 hour per character still.
House auction. Definitely.

Scams. Those too.

Mining, it really needs to be worked on. As do several trade skills.

NPC Vendors and PC Vendors.
Furniture, House Decor, House Addons.
Boats.
Monster spawn.
Town invasions (including those by PCs).
Support crew.
PvP, PK, Guilds, Factions, Friends.
Magery and other arcane stuff.
UOE/UOA stuff.
eBay, expect it.
No empty promises.
Account hacking/stealing.

This is getting too long and I'm getting bored.

------------------
If everyone loves a winner,
then I must be IR-RESISTABLE!

